:{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/#/schema/logo/image/","url":"https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/DDLogo.png","contentUrl":"https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/DDLogo.png","width":640,"height":853,"caption":"Damn Delicious"},"image":{"@id":"https://damndelicious.net/#/schema/logo/image/"},"sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/damndeliciousblog","https://www.instagram.com/damn_delicious/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/#/schema/person/0580fef3f191728c69dace28d2fac9ff","name":"Chungah","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/10524848b45fe7909c8148d8bf9e7a0e3726d514b29b95c8428148b2f01d4798?s=96&d=blank&r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/10524848b45fe7909c8148d8bf9e7a0e3726d514b29b95c8428148b2f01d4798?s=96&d=blank&r=g","contentUrl":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/10524848b45fe7909c8148d8bf9e7a0e3726d514b29b95c8428148b2f01d4798?s=96&d=blank&r=g","caption":"Chungah"},"description":"Chungah Rhee is the founder of Damn Delicious, a website created in 2011 featuring quick and easy meals. Chungah and her recipes are regularly featured in major media such as People, TODAY, and Bon Appetit, among others. Today, Chungah cooks nonstop alongside her two favorite corgi assistants, Butters and Cartman.","sameAs":["https://damndelicious.net/about-me/","https://www.facebook.com/damndeliciousblog","https://www.instagram.com/damn_delicious/","https://x.com/@damn_delicious"]},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266529755","position":1,"url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266529755","name":"I only have frozen salmon. How can I defrost salmon quickly?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Salmon can take about 12-24 hours to defrost in the refrigerator. For a quick defrost (about 1 hour), you can place the salmon in a resealable leak-proof bag, submerged in a bowl of cold water, changing out the water every 30 minutes.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266300578","position":2,"url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266300578","name":"Do I have to use white wine?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Additional chicken stock can be used for white wine as a non-alcoholic substitute.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266322755","position":3,"url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1724266322755","name":"What is half and half?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Half and half is equal parts of whole milk and cream. For 1 cup half and half, you can substitute 3/4 cup whole milk + 1/4 cup heavy cream or 2/3 cup skim or low-fat milk + 1/3 cup heavy cream.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1715620917648","position":4,"url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#faq-question-1715620917648","name":"What can I substitute for the spinach?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Kale, cabbage, swiss chard and collard greens are all great subs.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Salmon with Garlic Cream Sauce","author":{"@id":"https://damndelicious.net/#/schema/person/0580fef3f191728c69dace28d2fac9ff"},"description":"Perfectly pan-seared salmon served with the most irresistible garlicky cream sauce with sneaked in spinach!","datePublished":"2021-06-17T21:00:40+00:00","image":["https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Salmon-with-Garlic-Cream-SauceIMG_1398.jpg","https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Salmon-with-Garlic-Cream-SauceIMG_1398-500x500.jpg","https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Salmon-with-Garlic-Cream-SauceIMG_1398-500x375.jpg","https://damndelicious.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Salmon-with-Garlic-Cream-SauceIMG_1398-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Salmon with Garlic Cream Sauce","description":"Perfectly pan-seared salmon served with the most irresistible garlicky cream sauce with sneaked in spinach!","thumbnailUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/thumbs/lDSa6FUW-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https://content.jwplatform.com/videos/lDSa6FUW.mp4","uploadDate":"2024-04-25T11:35:42+00:00","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeIngredient":["4 (6-ounce) salmon fillets","Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper (to taste)","1 1/2 tablespoons unsalted butter","2 cloves garlic (minced)","1  medium shallot (diced)","2 tablespoons all-purpose flour","1/4 cup dry white wine*","3/4 cup chicken stock","3/4 cup half and half*","3 cups baby spinach","2 tablespoons chopped fresh dill","1  lemon (cut in wedges)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using paper towels, pat both sides of the salmon fillets dry; season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.","name":"Using paper towels, pat both sides of the salmon fillets dry; season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Melt butter in a large cast iron skillet over medium heat. Add salmon fillets to the skillet, skin side up, and cook until golden brown and a crust has formed, about 4-5 minutes. Using a fish turner, flip, and cook for an additional 4-5 minutes, or until desired doneness. Remove and keep warm.","name":"Melt butter in a large cast iron skillet over medium heat. Add salmon fillets to the skillet, skin side up, and cook until golden brown and a crust has formed, about 4-5 minutes. Using a fish turner, flip, and cook for an additional 4-5 minutes, or until desired doneness. Remove and keep warm.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Reduce heat to low; add garlic and shallots, and cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, about 2 minutes.","name":"Reduce heat to low; add garlic and shallots, and cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, about 2 minutes.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Whisk in flour until lightly browned, about 1 minute.","name":"Whisk in flour until lightly browned, about 1 minute.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in wine, scraping any browned bits from the bottom of the skillet.","name":"Stir in wine, scraping any browned bits from the bottom of the skillet.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in chicken stock and half and half until slightly thickened, about 2-3 minutes; season with salt and pepper, to taste.","name":"Stir in chicken stock and half and half until slightly thickened, about 2-3 minutes; season with salt and pepper, to taste.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in spinach until wilted, about 1-2 minutes. Return salmon to the skillet; sprinkle with dill.","name":"Stir in spinach until wilted, about 1-2 minutes. Return salmon to the skillet; sprinkle with dill.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve immediately with lemon wedges.","name":"Serve immediately with lemon wedges.","url":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#wprm-recipe-33678-step-0-7"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"39","reviewCount":"16"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This dish was so easy and was a hit with the whole family! Served with air fryer roasted potatoes.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Miriam"},"datePublished":"2025-12-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I am not very experienced cooking salmon. I followed the directions exactly. This was easy and so delicious!  Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Christy Smith"},"datePublished":"2025-11-17"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This salmon dish was SO delicious! It was quick and easy and presents like you spent much more time preparing it. I served with green beans and rice pilaf. Everyone loved it including the kids. 10/10 will definitely be making again.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"JB"},"datePublished":"2025-10-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Yummy! Didn't have spinach,  used Chard instead.  Didn't have fresh dill or lemon,  lol. Used fresh lemon balm instead.  No white wine either,  used more chicken broth.  Served with garden fresh oven roasted okra. It was delightful! Thanks for the recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dave"},"datePublished":"2025-09-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Very nice, made it in our Motorhome whilst away, easy, simple dish that can be 'tweaked' in various ways (I added a, teaspoon of dijon to the sauce)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jo Grimbo"},"datePublished":"2024-10-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was so very delicious. I added a little fresh linguini and shitake mushrooms from the farmer's market. I will make this often! Your site is a favorite of mine. Thanks.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jackie"},"datePublished":"2024-08-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Soooo good, even my 6 year ate it!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"CAROLINA ELLIS"},"datePublished":"2024-08-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Oh my goodness...how delicious is this?!  I used my cast iron pan for both the salmon and the sauce. The salmon was beautiful - crispy on the outside and so moist inside.  I doubled the sauce recipe and served it with Greek lemon rice.  Restaurant worthy!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Melanie Collins"},"datePublished":"2024-05-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have not made this yet…sounds very good and I will make it, but what’s the story with what pan to use?  You recommend a non-stick skillet and then in instructions you say to use a cast iron skillet?  So which one?  Think I’ll use the non-stick as I think the fish will stick to the cast iron, although I love cast iron or steel pans…","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carolyn Kotler"},"datePublished":"2024-02-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"HEB in Texas sells fresh, never frozen salmon as well as other fish like halibut, sole, red snapper...they'll label the fish as previously frozen if it has been frozen, and fresh, never frozen if it has never   been frozen. They get fresh salmon all year long. If it's wild-caught they will say so, if it's farmed they also let you know. Wild-caught is seasonal of course. The one we get most often is organic Norwegian salmon, really delicious. Or the Ora King salmon from New Zealand but you have to go Central Market for that. In California we also got fresh salmon; wild-caught was a little more common and a lot cheaper. Where you live may determine whether you can find fresh fish but it would be a surprise if most major markets didn't carry fresh, never frozen fish. Whole Foods carries fresh salmon, pretty sure.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Richard Kelly"},"datePublished":"2023-09-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I made this for dinner and my husband absolutely loved it.   We both enjoyed it.  I will be making this again in the future.  Thanks Chungah!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathy Ingram"},"datePublished":"2023-08-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My cousin and I just made this for dinner! Delicious! Thank you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"jill"},"datePublished":"2023-02-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was quick and easy and so delicious!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tara Dombrowsky"},"datePublished":"2022-11-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is such a great recipe - I've made it a few times for my family, and it's a hit. I don't change anything, except that I add more spinach and more dill. Serve with roasted fingerling potatoes to soak uptake sauce (a nice loaf of crusty bread would work, too). Easy enough for weeknights, but nice enough for guests.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shelby"},"datePublished":"2022-11-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this tonight. The echoes for seconds made it all worth it……tired working mom.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jolene"},"datePublished":"2022-10-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Oh my gosh, I made this tonight for 3 of us, and there is NONE left. Great recipe! Thanks :) Served it with brown jasmine rice, green salad and melon. Perfect.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Debbie Dillon"},"datePublished":"2022-09-05"}],"@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://damndelicious.net/2021/06/17/salmon-with-garlic-cream-sauce/"}]}</script>
